{"TopicId":209444,"ForumId":112,"TopicTitle":"Fuel UI","CreatedByName":"not giving a name","CreatedById":218458,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-08-21T00:24:01Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"not giving a name","CreatedById":218458,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-08-21T00:24:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBackground: In ksp intersteller mod, the WORST part of building rockets in matching fuel types, and I feel because the stock game is also losing siplity and adding more fuels, distinguishing which fuel tanks go with what engine, expectually if tanks can hold multiple types of fuel (refitting).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSolution:\u00A0 \u00A0A overlay for the vessel (like the f11 ui for heating) where tanks are colored based on their contents, and the engines/drains have the asssosiated color, think LOX engines are blue - mammoth engine blue,\u00A0 xenon green,\u00A0 ion engine green. It would be a simple solution , that would save a lot of confusion, and fit right along with f11 heat and f12 aerodynamics\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nimagine doing a mun landing, and getting stranded because your return stage uses a different fuel (happened to me in interstellar)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222022-08-21T13:08:00Z\u0022 title=\u002208/21/2022 01:08  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 21, 2022\u003C/time\u003E by not giving a name\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"t_v","CreatedById":213541,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-08-21T00:41:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI would like to see the fuel delivery overlay expanded with this, because for example, you can see fuel and electricity as separate colors, but different types of fuel are represented as the same thing (as far as I know). If this overlay gets an overhaul, it could also be used for other routing, like crew transferability if that is a thing that matters.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"intelliCom","CreatedById":209738,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-08-21T23:35:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224166045\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022209444\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221661041441\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022218458\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022not giving a name\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n23 hours ago, not giving a name said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSolution:\u00A0 \u00A0A overlay for the vessel (like the f11 ui for heating) where tanks are colored based on their contents, and the engines/drains have the asssosiated color, think LOX engines are blue - mammoth engine blue,\u00A0 xenon green,\u00A0 ion engine green.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBetter colour choices:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#cc0000;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERED\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u00A0- Kerosene\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#ff9900;\u0022\u003EYELLOW\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E - Oxidiser\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#3333ff;\u0022\u003EDARK BLUE\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E - LH2\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#66cccc;\u0022\u003ECYAN BLUE\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E - Xenon\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#33cc00;\u0022\u003EGREEN \u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E- Nuclear fuel\u00A0(if antimatter doesn\u0027t exist, then make this fission fuel)\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#cc33ff;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMAGENTA \u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E- Antimatter (if antimatter doesn\u0027t exist, then make this fusion fuel)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"whatsEJstandfor","CreatedById":220814,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-08-22T03:08:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224166365\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022209444\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221661124919\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022209738\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022intelliCom\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, intelliCom said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBetter colour choices:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat makes them necessarily better? Is there a kind of standard that already exists?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"intelliCom","CreatedById":209738,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-08-22T03:15:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224166396\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022209444\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221661137695\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022220814\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022whatsEJstandfor\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nJust now, whatsEJstandfor said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat makes them necessarily better? Is there a kind of standard that already exists?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust makes more sense from a user experience perspective. I mean, why make Xenon green instead of the colour of its exhaust material? Best to make the colours have useful associations with what they\u0027re related to instead of making them arbitrary. If you\u0027d like a standard referred to, then I\u0027m referring to the standard of what colours would be most applicable. These aren\u0027t hard and fast, since magenta could also be MPDs, green could also be methane, and yellow could be electricity.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Ember12","CreatedById":217583,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-08-23T01:02:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224166365\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022209444\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221661124919\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022209738\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022intelliCom\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 8/21/2022 at 4:35 PM, intelliCom said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBetter colour choices:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#cc0000;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERED\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u00A0- Kerosene\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#ff9900;\u0022\u003EYELLOW\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E - Oxidiser\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#3333ff;\u0022\u003EDARK BLUE\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E - LH2\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#66cccc;\u0022\u003ECYAN BLUE\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E - Xenon\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#33cc00;\u0022\u003EGREEN \u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E- Nuclear fuel\u00A0(if antimatter doesn\u0027t exist, then make this fission fuel)\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#cc33ff;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMAGENTA \u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E- Antimatter (if antimatter doesn\u0027t exist, then make this fusion fuel)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou might need a few more colors, for thing like Helium-3, metallic hydrogen, and whatever the \u0022torch-ships\u0022 will burn.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"intelliCom","CreatedById":209738,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-08-23T09:48:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224166633\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022209444\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221661216556\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022217583\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Ember12\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 hours ago, Ember12 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou might need a few more colors, for thing like Helium-3, metallic hydrogen, and whatever the \u0022torch-ships\u0022 will burn.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt gets to a point where it can be difficult to tell them apart if you have too many colours. I\u0027m pretty sure torchships are antimatter, which was listed in my original colours.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut, I\u0027ll give it a go nonetheless:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ctable border=\u00221\u0022 cellpadding=\u00221\u0022 cellspacing=\u00221\u0022 style=\u0022width:500px;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cthead\u003E\n\u003Ctr\u003E\n\u003Cth scope=\u0022col\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#ff0000;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERED (#ff0000)\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C